SOP: Rolling Mill Roll Gap Deviation, High Vibration, and Roll Neck Bearing Overheating

1. Notify the rolling mill superintendent and the control room operators.
2. Monitor roll-force cylinder pressure, roll-gap deviation, spindle vibration, and bearing temperatures.
3. If roll gap deviation exceeds 0.2mm or roll neck bearing temperature exceeds 90 C, abort the current strip and stop the mill.
4. Execute LOTO on the roll drive motor and isolate the roll-gap hydraulic power unit (HPU).
5. Inspect the work roll and backup roll surfaces for visual marking, scaling, or fire-cracking.
6. Verify hydraulic pressure stability and inspect roll-gap cylinders and servo valves for external oil leaks.
7. Inspect the roll cooling headers and verify water spray coverage is uniform and nozzles are clear.
8. Check roll neck bearing grease/mist lines and confirm no water contamination has occurred.
9. Perform zero-calibration of the roll-gap sensors (load cells and transducer alignment).
10. De-isolate, start roll drive under no-load, and run a test bar to confirm strip thickness and surface quality.
